<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-368-468  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 368 468.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  April 23 1990 n267 p63(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM's mixed European efforts. (plans for 1992 Europeanintegration) (Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hunter, Philip.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM has a two-part strategic plan for its international trade inlight of Europe's impending 1992 integration.andP;  The first part is a'market-driven management system' involving centralized planning,distributed operations, and sharing of information in bothdirections with business partners and customers.andP;  Improvedcustomer relations and smooth service across borders are at thecenter of the second objective.andP;  The criticisms of IBM's Europeanoperations include poor customer service, lack of communicationamong the IBM installations in the different countries and IBM'sdislike of open standards.andP;  IBM improves its sales statistics andimage with individual pricing of mainframe systems and its use ofgood third-party vendors for midrange systems.andP;  But even US-basedmultinationals are not always happy with the service provided byIBM's different units in Europe.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (international aspects).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     EuropeStrategic PlanningInternational TradeCustomer RelationsManagement.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>